## 2. Server Setup & Configuration

### 2.1 Express Application Setup
**File: `index.js`**

The main server file demonstrates professional Express.js application configuration:

```javascript
import express from "express";
import dotenv from "dotenv";
import cookieParser from "cookie-parser";
import cors from "cors";
import path from "path";

import { connectDB } from "./lib/db.js";
import authRoutes from "./routes/auth.route.js";
import messageRoutes from "./routes/message.route.js";
import { app, server } from "./lib/socket.js";

dotenv.config();

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5001;
const __dirname = path.resolve();

// Middleware Configuration
app.use(express.json());
app.use(cookieParser());
app.use(cors({
  origin: "http://localhost:5173",
  credentials: true,
}));

// API Routes
app.use("/api/auth", authRoutes);
app.use("/api/messages", messageRoutes);

// Production Static File Serving
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === "production") {
  app.use(express.static(path.join(__dirname, "../frontend/dist")));
  app.get("*", (req, res) => {
    res.sendFile(path.join(__dirname, "../frontend", "dist", "index.html"));
  });
}

// Server Initialization
server.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log("server is running on PORT:" + PORT);
  connectDB();
  console.log("JWT_SECRET:", process.env.JWT_SECRET);
});
```

**Advanced Concepts Explained:**

**Environment Variable Management:**
- `dotenv.config()` loads environment variables from .env file
- `process.env.PORT || 5001` provides fallback for deployment flexibility
- Sensitive configuration data kept separate from source code

**Middleware Stack Configuration:**
- `express.json()`: Parses incoming JSON payloads (built-in body parser)
- `cookieParser()`: Enables reading and setting HTTP cookies
- `cors()`: Configures Cross-Origin Resource Sharing for frontend communication

**CORS Configuration Deep Dive:**
```javascript
cors({
  origin: "http://localhost:5173",  // Specific origin for security
  credentials: true,                 // Allow cookies in cross-origin requests
})
```

**Route Mounting Strategy:**
- `/api/auth`: Authentication-related endpoints
- `/api/messages`: Message handling endpoints
- Prefix pattern provides API versioning capability

**Production Deployment Logic:**
- Static file serving for built frontend assets
- SPA (Single Page Application) fallback routing
- Environment-based conditional execution

### 2.2 Socket.io Integration Architecture
**File: `lib/socket.js`**

Real-time communication setup demonstrates advanced Socket.io concepts:

```javascript
import { Server } from "socket.io";
import http from "http";
import express from "express";

const app = express();
const server = http.createServer(app);

const io = new Server(server, {
  cors: {
    origin: ["http://localhost:5173"],
  },
});

// Online user tracking system
const userSocketMap = {}; // {userId: socketId}

export function getReceiverSocketId(userId) {
  return userSocketMap[userId];
}

io.on("connection", (socket) => {
  console.log("A user connected", socket.id);

  const userId = socket.handshake.query.userId;
  if (userId) userSocketMap[userId] = socket.id;

  // Broadcast online users to all clients
  io.emit("getOnlineUsers", Object.keys(userSocketMap));

  socket.on("disconnect", () => {
    console.log("A user disconnected", socket.id);
    delete userSocketMap[userId];
    io.emit("getOnlineUsers", Object.keys(userSocketMap));
  });
});

export { io, app, server };
```

**Socket.io Concepts Explained:**

**Server Initialization Pattern:**
- HTTP server creation using Node.js built-in http module
- Socket.io server attachment to existing HTTP server
- Express app integration for combined REST + WebSocket functionality

**Connection Lifecycle Management:**
- `connection` event: Triggered when client connects
- `disconnect` event: Triggered when client disconnects
- Automatic cleanup of user mapping on disconnect

**User Presence Tracking:**
- `userSocketMap`: In-memory storage of user-socket relationships
- Real-time broadcasting of online user lists
- Query parameter extraction for user identification

**Broadcasting Strategies:**
- `io.emit()`: Sends to all connected clients
- `io.to(socketId).emit()`: Sends to specific socket
- Event-driven communication pattern

