## 5. Message System & Real-time Communication

### 5.1 Message Controllers Implementation
**File: `controllers/message.controller.js`**

Comprehensive message handling with real-time features:

```javascript
import User from "../models/user.model.js";
import Message from "../models/message.model.js";
import cloudinary from "../lib/cloudinary.js";
import { getReceiverSocketId, io } from "../lib/socket.js";

export const getUsersForSidebar = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const loggedInUserId = req.user._id;
    const filteredUsers = await User.find({ _id: { $ne: loggedInUserId } }).select("-password");

    res.status(200).json(filteredUsers);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error in getUsersForSidebar: ", error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Internal server error" });
  }
};

export const getMessages = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { id: userToChatId } = req.params;
    const myId = req.user._id;

    const messages = await Message.find({
      $or: [
        { senderId: myId, receiverId: userToChatId },
        { senderId: userToChatId, receiverId: myId },
      ],
    });

    res.status(200).json(messages);
  } catch (error) {
    console.log("Error in getMessages controller: ", error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Internal server error" });
  }
};

export const sendMessage = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { text, image } = req.body;
    const { id: receiverId } = req.params;
    const senderId = req.user._id;

    let imageUrl;
    if (image) {
      const uploadResponse = await cloudinary.uploader.upload(image);
      imageUrl = uploadResponse.secure_url;
    }

    const newMessage = new Message({
      senderId,
      receiverId,
      text,
      image: imageUrl,
    });

    await newMessage.save();

    // Real-time message delivery
    const receiverSocketId = getReceiverSocketId(receiverId);
    if (receiverSocketId) {
      io.to(receiverSocketId).emit("newMessage", newMessage);
    }

    res.status(201).json(newMessage);
  } catch (error) {
    console.log("Error in sendMessage controller: ", error.message);
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Internal server error" });
  }
};
```

**Message System Concepts:**

**User Listing Logic:**
- `$ne` operator: MongoDB "not equal" for excluding current user
- Password exclusion for security
- Provides list of potential chat recipients

**Conversation Retrieval:**
- `$or` operator: MongoDB logical OR for bidirectional message search
- Finds messages where current user is either sender or receiver
- Enables complete conversation history

**Multi-media Message Support:**
- Text and image message handling
- Conditional image processing with Cloudinary
- Base64 to URL conversion for image storage

**Real-time Integration:**
- Socket.io integration for instant message delivery
- Receiver socket lookup by user ID
- Targeted message emission to specific user

**Database Operations:**
- Mongoose model operations (find, save)
- Asynchronous database interactions
- Error handling for all database operations

