## 7. API Routes & Architecture

### 7.1 Authentication Routes
**File: `routes/auth.route.js`**

RESTful API design with proper HTTP methods and middleware integration:

```javascript
import express from "express";
import { checkAuth, login, logout, signup, updateProfile } from "../controllers/auth.controller.js";
import { protectRoute } from "../middleware/auth.middleware.js";

const router = express.Router();

// Public routes
router.post("/signup", signup);
router.post("/login", login);
router.post("/logout", logout);

// Protected routes
router.put("/update-profile", protectRoute, updateProfile);
router.get("/check", protectRoute, checkAuth);

export default router;
```

**REST API Design Principles:**

**HTTP Method Usage:**
- `POST /signup`: User registration (creates new resource)
- `POST /login`: User authentication (creates session)
- `POST /logout`: Session termination (modifies session state)
- `PUT /update-profile`: User data modification (updates existing resource)
- `GET /check`: Authentication status retrieval (reads data)

**Route Protection Strategy:**
- Public routes: No authentication required
- Protected routes: Require valid JWT token
- Middleware composition for security layers

**Express Router Benefits:**
- Modular route organization
- Middleware stacking capabilities
- Namespace isolation (auth vs messages)

### 7.2 Message Routes
**File: `routes/message.route.js`**

Message handling with parameter-based routing:

```javascript
import express from "express";
import { protectRoute } from "../middleware/auth.middleware.js";
import { getMessages, getUsersForSidebar, sendMessage } from "../controllers/message.controller.js";

const router = express.Router();

// All message routes require authentication
router.get("/users", protectRoute, getUsersForSidebar);
router.get("/:id", protectRoute, getMessages);
router.post("/send/:id", protectRoute, sendMessage);

export default router;
```

**Advanced Routing Concepts:**

**Parameter Routing:**
- `/:id`: Dynamic route parameter for user/conversation ID
- RESTful URL structure for resource identification
- Parameter extraction in controllers via `req.params`

**Route Hierarchy:**
- `/users`: List all available chat users
- `/:id`: Get conversation with specific user
- `/send/:id`: Send message to specific user

**Consistent Protection:**
- All message routes require authentication
- Uniform security enforcement
- User context available in all controllers

